java is a programming language and also a platform used to build software like
web applications, mobile apps , desktop apps and backend systems
what is java ?
object-oriented programming language 
Platform-independent(write once , run anywhere)
used mainly for backend development 
why java is popular?
easy to learn(compared to many languages)
very secure 
runs on any system( windows,linux,Mac)
Used in big companies 
perfect for spring boot 
How Java works
u write code in .java file 
Java compiler converts it to bytecode(.class)
JVM(Java Virtual Machine) runs that bytecode 
Because of JVM , java code runs on any OS.
where Java is used?
Web applications(Spring Boot)
Android apps
Banking & finance systems
Cloud & microservices
Desktop apps

class Hello {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
   System.out.println("Hello Java");
}
}

